Package jbt.execution.core

Interface Summary
IBTExecutor A behaviour tree executor (entity that is able to run a behaviour tree) must implement this interface.
IBTLibrary Common interface for all behaviour tree libraries.
IContext Interface defining the context of a behavior tree task.
ITaskState The ITaskState interface represents the persistent state of a task in a behaviour tree.
 

Class Summary
BTExecutor BTExecutor is the implementation of the IBTExecutor interface.
BTExecutorFactory The BTExecutorFactory implements the simple factory pattern, and allows clients of the framework to create instances of IBTExecutor objects that will run specific behaviour trees.
BTLibraryFactory The BTLibraryFactory implements the simple factory pattern, and allows clients of the framework to create instances of IBTLibrary composed of behaviour trees.
ContextFactory The ContextFactory implements the simple factory pattern, and allows clients of the framework to create instances of IContext objects that can be used when running behaviour trees.
ExecutionTask A behaviour tree is conceptually modeled by the ModelTask class.
TaskState Default implementation of the ITaskState interface.
TaskStateFactory The TaskStateFactory implements the simple factory pattern, and allows clients of the framework to create instances of ITaskState objects.
 

Enum Summary
BTExecutor.BTExecutorList Enum defining the relevant lists that the BTExecutor handles.
ExecutionTask.Status Enum defining the possible states of an ExecutionTask.
